Well, this is the plane I'm flying today.
Complaint One: We need a cute flight logbook. Black is too boring, and pink is not actually pink, but rather salmon red.
I have always wanted to fly since I was a child.
Today, my dream came true... I flew a plane today. I'm still in shock and haven't quite gotten over it yet.
FlightAware's data.
I plan to try again this Saturday. The weather doesn't look very good now, but today is just Monday.
It seems that challenges in this area have already begun to emerge. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may find it difficult to obtain a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it would require a great deal of time and a lot of extra work.
Although this is a bit discouraging, it's just another problem that needs to be solved, and it seems to be solvable at the moment. It just requires a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I will face next:
The FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't be able to get a medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I ever have the opportunity to customize an airplane's tail number, it must be some variation of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun will rise as usual when I'm not around, haha. That's really disappointing.
I have to fly up again. But this lousy weather is really not cooperating.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
